---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <div class="project-detail-page project-detail-layout">
    <div class="project-detail-content">
    <section class="project-detail-hero" id="project-summary">
      <a class="project-detail-back-link" href="/projects">← Back to Projects</a>
      <h1>Sim-ester | E-Commerce Website</h1>
      <p class="project-detail-meta">Associated with: UBC Okanagan - COSC 304</p>
      <p class="project-detail-stack-label">Tech Stack</p>
      <div class="project-detail-stack-list">
        <span>Node.js</span>
        <span>Express</span>
        <span>PostgreSQL</span>
        <span>Neon</span>
        <span>Render</span>
        <span>Docker</span>
        <span>SendGrid</span>
      </div>
      <p>
        Sim-ester is an online store built for the COSC 304 project. It is a dynamic, database integrated web application that use Node.js, Express.js, and SQL.
        Key features included product listings, filtered search, order history, and administrative tools. It showcases simulation-style games based on courses 
        at UBC Okanagan and includes a full shopping flow from browsing to checkout.
        </p>
        <p>
            We designed and implemented the database schema, used prepared statements for secure SQL queries, and built a clean, intuitive UI for seamless user 
            interaction. The project was developed using Node.js, HTML/CSS, and Microsoft SQL Server.
        </p>
      <p>
        Sim-ester placed 1st overall among over 100 projects in the course, demonstrating both technical proficiency and strong design.
      </p>
      <div class="project-detail-links">
        <a class="project-detail-link" href="https://github.com/LZBTH16/sim-ester" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="project-detail-grid">
      <article class="card project-detail-card" id="project-features">
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <ul class="project-detail-list">
          <li>Product listings: Display products with images, descriptions, and pricing.</li>
          <li>Ratings and reviews: Allow customers to rate and review purchased products.</li>
          <li>Search and filter: Find products by name and filter results by category.</li>
          <li>Order history: View past orders with details such as products, purchase date, and order total.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card project-detail-card" id="project-role">
        <h2>My Role</h2>
        <p>
          I focused on front-end design and key application features. I designed and implemented the site’s UI across all pages, ensuring a consistent and 
          user-friendly experience. I also built core functionality for product listings, customer management, and admin tools (add/update/delete products),
           and contributed to server-side logic and ongoing code improvements.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <article class="card project-detail-card project-detail-screenshots-card" id="project-screenshots">
      <h2>Screenshots</h2>
      <div class="project-detail-screenshots">
        <figure class="project-screenshot-card">
          <img class="project-screenshot-image" src="/images/projects/sim-ester/home-page-1.png" alt="Sim-ester home page screenshot 1" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Home Page 1</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="project-screenshot-card">
          <img class="project-screenshot-image" src="/images/projects/sim-ester/home-page-2.png" alt="Sim-ester home page screenshot 2" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Home Page 2</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="project-screenshot-card">
          <img class="project-screenshot-image" src="/images/projects/sim-ester/products.png" alt="Sim-ester products page screenshot" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Products</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="project-screenshot-card">
          <img class="project-screenshot-image" src="/images/projects/sim-ester/product-example.png" alt="Sim-ester product example screenshot" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Product Example</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="project-screenshot-card">
          <img class="project-screenshot-image" src="/images/projects/sim-ester/product-reviews.png" alt="Sim-ester product reviews screenshot" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Product Reviews</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="project-screenshot-card">
          <img class="project-screenshot-image" src="/images/projects/sim-ester/shopping-cart.png" alt="Sim-ester shopping cart screenshot" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Shopping Cart</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="project-screenshot-card">
          <img class="project-screenshot-image" src="/images/projects/sim-ester/order-summary.png" alt="Sim-ester order summary screenshot" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Order Summary</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="project-screenshot-card">
          <img class="project-screenshot-image" src="/images/projects/sim-ester/profile.png" alt="Sim-ester profile screenshot" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Profile</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </article>
    </div>

    <aside class="project-detail-toc" aria-label="On this page">
      <h2 class="project-detail-toc-title">On This Page</h2>
      <nav>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="#project-summary">Summary</a></li>
          <li><a href="#project-features">Features</a></li>
          <li><a href="#project-role">My Role</a></li>
          <li><a href="#project-screenshots">Screenshots</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
